<hr/>
<p class="lead">The PIP clinic focuses on serving public interests through applied research, experiential learning, and community based organizing. We achieve this by partnering with advocates, mutual aid organizations, and special-interest groups, as well as local governments throughout the Puget Sound region. Our current work is focused on digital civic infrastructure, digital privacy, and labor policy.</p>
<hr/>
<h2>Mission</h2>
<p>Our mission is to cooperatively
Build just and fair technologies that serve the public interest 
Advocate for and inform the development of public policies 
Facilitate experiential learning opportunities to build a new coalition of public technologists </p>
<h2>Vision</h2>
<p>A growing coalition of technologists, educators, researchers, and community organizations cooperatively advancing the public interest to face the escalating crises of postmodernity 
</p>
